President Trump welcomed NATO Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg to the White House to discuss NATO's efforts in addressing security challenges. Trump highlighted the importance of burden-sharing among NATO members and applauded the increase in defense spending by Allies. He also praised the success in the fight against ISIS, particularly in Syria. Secretary General Stoltenberg expressed gratitude for Trump's support and emphasized the need for continued investment in defense. He also highlighted NATO's participation in the fight against terrorism and support for finding a peaceful solution to the Afghanistan crisis. Vice President Mike Pence and other officials also expressed their appreciation for NATO's strengthened alliance under Trump's leadership. The meeting touched on topics such as Afghanistan, Russia's violation of the INF Treaty, and China's involvement in Venezuela.